duck: Abyssinia (battle honour) - Abyssinia is a battle honour awarded to units of the British Indian Army and the British Army which participated in the 1868 campaign to free Europeans held hostage in Abyssinia by Emperor Tewod...
Abyssinia (musical) - Abyssinia is a musical with music by Ted Kociolek, lyrics by James Racheff, and a book by both Racheff and Kociolek, based on the novel Marked by Fire, by Joyce Carol Thomas.

wiki.text:
'Abyssinia' may refer to:
* Ethiopia, the modern nation
* Ethiopian Empire, an historical nation
* SS ''Abyssinia'', 1870 Canadian Pacific steamship
* HMS ''Abyssinia'' (1870), British armoured ship
* ''Abyssinia'' (musical)
* Abyssinia (battle honour)
* A song by the Patti Smith Group on [[Radio Ethiopia]]
